social_posts.post_text: Today, I officially retire from pro sports. After four years in the @mls and seven years in the @nfl, there have been many memories made as well as a few regrets, but I’m thrilled to be moving on to my next stage of life as a speaker and author. Thank you to all of my teammates and a few select coaches. Thank you to the fans that cheered me on and supported me through good and bad. Thank you @fcdallas @chargers @jaguars for giving me a chance to prove myself on the field. All love, all the best- Josh Lambo

Part 1 of the Lambo expedition & photo workshop. 
I drove up from Denver through the Kansas countryside through the morning. Josh had spent the night just outside the park on BLM land. We met at a gas station just outside the East entrance to the park before exploring for a bit inside. It was a hot & hazy day. The flies were abundant. Between all that & given the dogs’ inability to explore in the National Parks, we opted to jet out the Black Hills to gain some shade & elevation pretty quickly.

social_posts.post_text: The ultimate adventure tee with the ultimate adventure pup ✌🏼

We can learn so much from Pro Athletes… from their successes, approaches to overcoming challenges, game plans for peak performance… and everything in between.

I feel incredibly honored to be a conduit… helping bring those journeys, stories and lessons forward so they can impact at the highest levels during their playing careers, and long after game-day!!

@joshlambo4 is one of those players - a dual pro sport athlete (NFL & MLS). He’s cracked a code to reach peak physical and emotional performance, and now shares his signature approach from the stage.

To describe his speaking style in 3 words:

☑️ Personable
☑️ Self-Aware
☑️ Funny

We were fortunate to capture all of it at our Pro Speaker Experience in Charlotte - a VIP Public Speaking Coaching & Performance Camp. 

I appreciate Josh for entrusting his transition to a Professional Speaking career to me and our Coached by B team!!

Coach B / Dr. Barb

#atletespeaker
#drbarb
#speakercoach

Get an inside look into our upcoming Renew Your Resilience Summit with this sneak peek from former @mls and @nfl player @joshlambo4 👀 This 4-day online event from Dec. 12-15 will feature 20 top experts equipped to help you bounce back from adversity and maximize your potential. 💥 Grab your FREE spot now using the link in bio! ✅

Josh remembers: “I was a goalkeeper for a reason. I didn’t want to run. 🏃‍♂️ I wanted to play soccer but I didn’t want to run. And you can get away with it at the club level but when you get to your national team, there’s no avoiding it. 😅 You got to work. And so I’m letting up more goals than I ever have, I’m literally the least fit person on the whole team. 😖 And I’m starting to think to myself ‘Man, maybe the coaching staff got it wrong. Maybe I don’t belong here.’” 🤔🤷‍♂️

👟 Former @mls Pro and @nfl kicker @joshlambo4 talking about his experience with “stinkin’ thinkin’ 💭 

“It might not be the best way to think. 🧠 And I experienced this again when I got to the NFL. My first two years in the league weren’t very great. 😕 I was, you know, a bottom third kicker in terms of percentage. 📉 I’m going into my third year, I’m playing for the Chargers, and they bring in another kicker to compete against me in preseason. 🏈 And the reason why I wasn’t doing so hot, the reason why I was missing these kicks my first two years, was I was my mind was just flooded with negative thoughts. 😱 Every time I stepped on in the field I heard in my head, “You aren’t good enough. This kick is too far. 🏈 You’ve never made one this far before. The wind just picked up. You’re not experienced enough. You don’t have enough kicks to be in this league.” 😤😤😤

I love photography. I love watches. I love mash-ups of things that don’t normally go together- like a soccer player that played football lol. I challenge you to do what you love, regardless of what other people think about it. Make music you would listen to. Take a picture you’d want to stop scrolling to look at. Produce a film you’d take the time to watch yourself. Do what you love, and others will love you for it. If they don’t, then as Ted Lasso says- be a goldfish #InstaTeam #WatchFam
